  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h4>We ensure the safety of all students in a number of different ways:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Our college requires students to wear lanyards with photo-card ID in order to gain entry onto our campuses</li>
<li>All students have access to our specialist Safeguarding Team who are on hand to support with any issue, including well-being and counselling experts</li>
<li>Every member of staff receives regular safeguarding training and raise concerns or report issues relating to safeguarding and welfare</li>
<li>We are committed to creating a culture where British Values are promoted and practiced in all aspects of college life, in line with the Government’s counter terrorism strategy - Prevent</li>
<li>All staff are DBS (Disclosure and Barring Service looking for criminal records) checked; without this approval staff will not be allowed any access in the college without supervision</li>
<li>The college provides a safe and friendly learning environment compliant with UK Health and Safety legislation</li>
<li>CCTV is installed at various points around the campuses.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h4><strong>Want to find out more?</strong></h4>
<p>If you would like to find out more about how we keep our students safe, please view the following policies:</p>
<ul>
<li><a data-udi="umb://document/d35eff9dfff54be7b8821634cecdafea" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d35eff9dfff54be7b8821634cecdafea}" title="Equality &amp; Diversity">Equality and Diversity</a></li>
<li><a data-udi="umb://document/8b3bf2d45aa844b69d7a56f88b420281" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8b3bf2d45aa844b69d7a56f88b420281}" title="Policies">Guidance on radicalisation and extremism</a></li>
<li><a data-udi="umb://document/8b3bf2d45aa844b69d7a56f88b420281" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8b3bf2d45aa844b69d7a56f88b420281}" title="Policies">Safeguarding Policy.</a></li>
</ul>]]></mainContent>
